args.CodeContent:
# Implementation Plan - Nix-Native AI Stack & Open WebUI Integration

Transitioning the AI stack on your NixOS system from the Electron-based **Jan** app to a highly integrated, resource-efficient, and declarative **Nix-native AI stack** consisting of Ollama, Antigravity, Gemini, and the **Open WebUI** service.

---

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> **Open WebUI Configuration & Access**:
> We will enable the native `services.open-webui` NixOS module, which hosts a web server at `http://localhost:8080` out-of-the-box.
> * **Local Ollama Integration**: Open WebUI will automatically detect and connect to your existing CUDA-accelerated native Ollama service.
> * **Gemini API Integration**: You can easily connect Gemini frontier models by pasting your Google AI Studio API key directly into Open WebUI's browser settings panel (`Admin Settings` > `Connections` > `OpenAI`), bypassing the need to store secrets in your Nix configuration.

---

## Proposed Changes

We will remove the unneeded Electron app `jan` and spin up the native `open-webui` daemon.

### 1. NixOS System Configuration

#### [MODIFY] [configuration.nix](file:///home/nondeus/.nix-config/nixos/configuration.nix)
* Enable the native `open-webui` service and map it to your local GPU-accelerated Ollama:
  ```nix
  # Application Support
  services = {
    # Open WebUI Service
    open-webui = {
      enable = true;
      port = 8080;
      environment = {
        OLLAMA_API_BASE_URL = "http://127.0.0.1:11434";
      };
    };

    # Ollama Service
    ollama = {
      enable = true;
      package = pkgs.ollama-cuda;
      home = "/home/nondeus";
      models = "/home/nondeus/Storage/ollama/models";
    };
    # ... other services ...
  };
  ```

---

### 2. Home Manager User Configuration

#### [MODIFY] [pkgs.nix](file:///home/nondeus/.nix-config/home/pkgs.nix)
* Remove `jan` from `home.packages` to clean up the Electron-based app and free resources:
  ```diff
  - jan
  ```

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Build Verification
1. Run a dry-run of the NixOS flake to ensure no syntax or module evaluation errors:
   ```bash
   nix build .#nixosConfigurations.nondeus.config.system.build.toplevel --dry-run
   ```

### Manual Verification
1. Rebuild the system configuration.
2. Verify the new Open WebUI service is running:
   ```bash
   systemctl status open-webui.service
   ```
3. Open Brave Browser and navigate to `http://localhost:8080`.
4. Sign up (the first account created is automatically designated the Admin).
5. Verify local models loaded in Ollama are immediately available in the top-left dropdown model selector.
6. Connect Gemini frontier models by navigating to **Admin Settings > Connections > OpenAI**, adding the base URL `https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/openai`, and pasting your AI Studio API key.

