### Installation Steps on the Samsung Galaxy S26 Ultra

#### A. Install Nix-on-Droid App
Do not install Termux or Nix-on-Droid from the Google Play Store as API restriction limits on newer Android targets block binary execution inside proot. Download the installation package directly from **F-Droid** or download compiled files from the official Nix-on-Droid GitHub releases catalog.

#### B. Initialize and Bootstrap
1.  Open the Nix-on-Droid application. It automatically downloads and builds the standard bootstrap environment.
2.  After the initial bootstrap has successfully loaded the command prompt, update the channel manifest:
    ```bash
    nix-channel --update
    ```

#### C. Configure Git & SSH Access
Pulling files from your private repository requires configuring keys. Generate a dedicated device key in the local proot shell:
```bash
nix-shell -p openssh --run "ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C 's26-ultra-droid'"
cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub
```
Add the returned public key text to your Git hosting account's authorized keys index.

#### D. Clone and Activate the Configuration Flake
Run a temporary shell instance containing Git, download your configuration repository, and evaluate the setup:
```bash
nix-shell -p git --run "git clone git@github.com:lowcache/infernalnixos.git ~/.nix-config"
cd ~/.nix-config
```
To activate, trigger the activation build using the `--impure` flag. The proot container references files at fixed, dynamic paths outside standard sandboxes, which prevents evaluation under standard pure rules:
```bash
nix-on-droid switch --flake .#default --impure
```

